        <h2>Requirements</h2>

        <p>The ALC is a multi-channel learning centre supporting European aviation. They wanted to <strong>promote how successful</strong> they had been in attracting learners. They came up with the idea of showing some KPI statistics on the <a href="https://learningzone.eurocontrol.int/" target="_blank">Learning Zone</a> home page.</p>

        <p>The panel needed to be attractive and show multiple statistics, while not taking up too much space.</p>

        <h2>Restrictions</h2>

        <p>The Learning Zone home page is built on the <a href="https://www.im-c.com/learning-suite/" target="_blank">IMC Learning Management System</a>. It is made up of 'panels' that are 'injected' into the home page on the server but cannot include data from the back-end. All the CSS and JavaScript in these panels can have an effect on the rest of the page if we are not careful ({% include "../../_shared/images/icons/icon-warning-filled.svg" %} Danger! Danger! {% include "../../_shared/images/icons/icon-warning-filled.svg" %})</p>

