        <p>To highlight the worldwide appeal of the platform, we decided to plot the number of visitors from each country on a rotating globe.
        </p>

        <p>Note the use of public/private panel popup</p>

        <p>We created a panel template using <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/" target="_blank">11ty</a>. During development we can see the results as a stand alone page. For production, only the HTML needed for the panel is output along with bundled and namespaced CSS and JavaScript.</p>

        <p>The panel uses semantic HTML and <strong>vanilla</strong> CSS and JavaScript - the default choice at Rising Sky.</p>

        <p>As we couldn't get the data from the back-end on load, the statistics are <strong>fetched from an API</strong>.</p>

        <p>The page is <strong>responsive</strong> along two axes: screen size and logged in status.</p>

        <p>For logged out users, the row showing user specific data is removed. For users on smaller screens, the globe is also removed, otherwise the panel would take up too much room, forcing learners to scroll more before getting to the content they need.</p>

